statements: SELECT * FROM calibration_logs;
SELECT log_id, sensor_id, calibration_date FROM calibration_logs WHERE sensor_id = 1;
SELECT log_id, sensor_id, calibration_result FROM calibration_logs WHERE calibration_result > 0.9;
SELECT * FROM calibration_logs ORDER BY calibration_date DESC;
SELECT technician_name, COUNT(*) AS total_logs FROM calibration_logs GROUP BY technician_name;
SELECT * FROM calibration_logs WHERE sensor_id = 123 ORDER BY calibration_date DESC;
SELECT calibration_result, technician_name FROM calibration_logs WHERE calibration_result > 5 AND technician_name LIKE 'John%' ORDER BY sensor_id;
SELECT DISTINCT sensor_id, COUNT(log_id) FROM calibration_logs GROUP BY sensor_id HAVING COUNT(log_id) > 10;
SELECT AVG(calibration_result) AS avg_result, MIN(calibration_result) AS min_result, MAX(calibration_result) AS max_result FROM calibration_logs;

SELECT sensor_id, EXTRACT(MONTH FROM calibration_date) AS month, COUNT(log_id) AS num_logs FROM calibration_logs GROUP BY sensor_id, EXTRACT(MONTH FROM calibration_date) ORDER BY sensor_id, month DESC;

SELECT c.log_id, c.calibration_date, s.manufacturer FROM calibration_logs c JOIN sensors s ON c.sensor_id = s.sensor_id;
SELECT t.first_name, t.last_name, cr.result FROM technicians t JOIN calibration_results cr ON t.technician_id = cr.technician_id WHERE cr.result = TRUE;

SELECT cp.procedure_name, COUNT(cr.result) FROM calibration_procedures cp LEFT JOIN calibration_results cr ON cp.procedure_id = cr.procedure_id GROUP BY cp.procedure_name ORDER BY COUNT(cr.result) DESC;
